{{multiple image | direction = vertical | width = 425 | image1 = Metorolinkca.logo.png | alt1 = Metrolink logo | image2 = F59PH 860 High resolution.JPG | alt2 = A Metrolink train pulls into the Irvine station. | caption2 = A Metrolink train pulls into the Irvine station. }}
Metrolink is a commuter rail system serving five counties in the southern California area. The system is centered at Los Angeles Union Station, with seven of its eight lines terminating there. Metrolink trains arrive less often than [[Getting around Los Angeles by Rail/Metro Rail|Metro Rail]] trains, and unlike the Metro Rail trains, they depart on specific schedules. (These schedules can be found [http://www.metrolinktrains.com/schedules/ here].)
==Subpages== * [[Getting around Los Angeles by Rail/Metrolink/Ventura County Line|Ventura County Line]] * [[Getting around Los Angeles by Rail/Metrolink/Antelope Valley Line|Antelope Valley Line]] * [[Getting around Los Angeles by Rail/Metrolink/San Bernardino Line|San Bernardino Line]] * [[Getting around Los Angeles by Rail/Metrolink/Riverside Line|Riverside Line]] * [[Getting around Los Angeles by Rail/Metrolink/Orange County Line|Orange County Line]] * [[Getting around Los Angeles by Rail/Metrolink/Inland Empire-Orange County Line|Inland Empire-Orange County Line]] * [[Getting around Los Angeles by Rail/Metrolink/91 Line|91 Line]] * [[Getting around Los Angeles by Rail/Metrolink/Burbank-Bob Hope Airport Line|Burbank-Bob Hope Airport LIne]]
==System Map== [[File:Metrolink.png|alt=Metrolink system map|950px]]
