=== Usage ===
This template alerts readers that parts of a page have moved to avoid confusing people studying a book while it is going through reorganization efforts.

''Arguments'' for the template (all arguments are optional):
* The '''first three unnamed arguments''' are the names of the pages where sections have moved to. Pages are linked to automatically.
* '''comment1''', '''comment2''', '''comment3''' provide a way to comment on each destination page, for instance, explaining what contents was moved to each page.
* '''others''' if there are more than three destination pages. Argument is displayed as is, so manual formating and linking are required.

=== Example ===
<tt><nowiki>{{Modulesplit|Haskell/Other data structures|comment1=for the discussions of trees and general map/fold functions.}}</nowiki></tt>

{{Modulesplit|Haskell/Other data structures|comment1=for the discussions of trees and general map/fold functions.}}

